&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;h3 id="what-is-usememo">What is useMemo?
&lt;/h3>&lt;p>useMemo is a React hook that caches calculation results and reuses them when needed. It eliminates redundant computations when a function is called with identical inputs. It consists of two essential elements:&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Calculation Function&lt;/strong>: A function that performs computations and returns a value to be cached.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Dependency Array&lt;/strong>: A list of values that, when modified, trigger a recalculation.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;p>During component re-renders, React verifies if dependencies have changed. If they remain the same, it skips the calculation entirely and uses the previously cached result.&lt;/p>
