&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="c1">// React.memo prevents re-rendering if props haven&amp;#39;t changed
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="c1">&lt;/span>&lt;span class="kr">const&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nx">OptimizedChild&lt;/span> &lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nx">React&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">memo&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">(&lt;/span>&lt;span class="kd">function&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">({&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nx">userInfo&lt;/span> &lt;span class="p">})&lt;/span> &lt;span class="p">{&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> &lt;span class="nx">console&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">log&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">(&lt;/span>&lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;Child component rendering&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">);&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> &lt;span class="k">return&lt;/span> &lt;span class="p">&amp;lt;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">div&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;{&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">userInfo&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nx">details&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">}&amp;lt;/&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">div&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="p">});&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>In React, each render creates objects with new memory addresses. Since React performs reference comparisons for objects, this behavior triggers re-renders even when the actual content remains unchanged.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>By implementing useMemo, we maintain consistent object references unless dependencies actually change, effectively preventing unnecessary re-renders in memoized child components.&lt;/p>
