&lt;h2 id="conclusion">Conclusion
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>The useMemo hook stands as one of React&amp;rsquo;s most valuable performance optimization tools, enabling you to cache expensive calculations and maintain stable object references. Rather than applying it indiscriminately, target specific performance bottlenecks such as complex data transformations and objects passed to memoized components.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>By implementing these techniques strategically, you can build React applications that maintain responsiveness and performance, even as your data complexity and UI requirements grow.&lt;/p>
